8.22	Confederation_bridge	Confederation Bridge	The Confederation Bridge (French: ) is a bridge spanning the Abegweit Passage of Northumberland Strait, linking Prince Edward Island with mainland New Brunswick, Canada. It was commonly referred to as the "Fixed Link" by residents of Prince Edward Island prior to its official naming. Construction took place from the autumn of 1993 to the spring of 1997, costing C$1.3 billion. The 12.9-kilometre (8 mi) long bridge opened on 31 May 1997.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/92/Confederation_Bridge_2007.jpg/250px-Confederation_Bridge_2007.jpg
